1
00:00:04,104 --> 00:00:06,137
<i>-ONCE UPON A TIME...</i>

2
00:00:06,137 --> 00:00:10,870
<i>THERE WAS A GIRL WHO LOVED</i>
<i>TO DANCE VERY MUCH.</i>

3
00:00:10,870 --> 00:00:12,537
<i>THE GIRL MADE THE MISTAKE</i>

4
00:00:12,537 --> 00:00:16,070
<i>OF PUTTING ON A PAIR</i>
<i>OF RED SHOES THAT, ONCE PUT ON,</i>

5
00:00:16,070 --> 00:00:20,170
<i>WOULD FORCE HER TO DANCE</i>
<i>FOR ETERNITY.</i>

6
00:00:20,170 --> 00:00:24,870
<i>THE GIRL CONTINUED TO DANCE</i>
<i>DAY AND NIGHT.</i>

7
00:00:24,870 --> 00:00:26,570
<i>OOPS.</i>

8
00:00:26,570 --> 00:00:29,737
<i>THIS IS A DIFFERENT STORY.</i>

9
00:00:29,737 --> 00:00:32,670
<i>ALTHOUGH, PERHAPS IT IS NOT</i>

10
00:00:32,670 --> 00:00:37,537
<i>SO COMPLETELY DIFFERENT</i>
<i>AFTER ALL.</i>

11
00:00:40,804 --> 00:00:43,837
[ RITSUKO OKAZAKI'S
"MORNING GRACE" PLAYING ]

12
00:00:54,770 --> 00:00:59,804
<i>-♪ YONDE IRU KOE ♪</i>

13
00:00:59,804 --> 00:01:05,570
<i>♪ SAA ME O SAMASHITE ♪</i>

14
00:01:05,570 --> 00:01:11,204
<i>♪ NAKIGAO NUGUTTE ♪</i>

15
00:01:11,204 --> 00:01:14,537
<i>♪ MABUSHII HIKARI ♪</i>

16
00:01:14,537 --> 00:01:17,704
<i>♪ KIGI NO TSUYU ♪</i>

17
00:01:17,704 --> 00:01:22,970
<i>♪ UMARERU ♪</i>

18
00:01:22,970 --> 00:01:27,904
<i>♪ DARE MO SHIRANAI ♪</i>

19
00:01:27,904 --> 00:01:33,270
<i>♪ HIMITSU NO MIZUBE DE ♪</i>

20
00:01:33,270 --> 00:01:38,237
<i>♪ ODORE INOCHI NO PA DO DU ♪</i>

21
00:01:38,237 --> 00:01:43,837
<i>♪ KYOU MO YUME MITERU ♪</i>

22
00:01:43,837 --> 00:01:48,770
<i>♪ SORE WA YASASHIKU ♪</i>

23
00:01:48,770 --> 00:01:54,070
<i>♪ HAGESHII NAGARE NE ♪</i>

24
00:01:54,070 --> 00:01:59,037
<i>♪ DOKO MADE TSUZUKU RABIRINSU ♪</i>

25
00:01:59,037 --> 00:02:03,704
<i>♪ WATASHI WA YUKOU ♪</i>

26
00:02:03,704 --> 00:02:08,470
<i>♪ NIGIRISHIMERU YUME ♪</i>

27
00:02:08,470 --> 00:02:11,504
[ TCHAIKOVSKY'S
"WALTZ OF THE FLOWERS" PLAYING ]

28
00:02:30,161 --> 00:02:33,694
-[ GASPS ]
-WHAT DO YOU THINK OF ME?

29
00:02:33,694 --> 00:02:35,927
I WANT TO KNOW.

30
00:02:35,927 --> 00:02:40,061
-I...UH, I...

31
00:02:40,061 --> 00:02:44,561
<i>[ Thinking ] I'M A DUCK.</i>
<i>I'M REALLY ONLY A BIRD.</i>

32
00:02:44,561 --> 00:02:47,161
<i>BUT WHAT THE PRINCE SEES</i>
<i>IS PRINCESS TUTU</i>

33
00:02:47,161 --> 00:02:49,527
<i>IN HER BEAUTIFUL DRESS.</i>

34
00:02:49,527 --> 00:02:51,561
<i>IT'S NOT ME.</i>

35
00:02:51,561 --> 00:02:56,994
[ WATER FLOWING ]

36
00:02:56,994 --> 00:03:00,227
-WHAT DID I DO JUST NOW?

37
00:03:00,227 --> 00:03:03,261
[ WATER FLOWING ]

38
00:03:11,227 --> 00:03:16,161
[ RAVENS CAWING ]

39
00:03:16,161 --> 00:03:19,194
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

40
00:03:24,561 --> 00:03:27,227
-[ GROANS ]

41
00:03:27,227 --> 00:03:28,861
<i>[ Thinking ] SOME THINGS</i>
<i>JUST DON'T CHANGE</i>

42
00:03:28,861 --> 00:03:30,361
<i>AFTER A NIGHT'S SLEEP.</i>

43
00:03:30,361 --> 00:03:32,994
<i>RUE AND MYTHO ARE STILL</i>
<i>PERFECT FOR EACH OTHER.</i>

44
00:03:32,994 --> 00:03:35,027
<i>FAKIR IS STILL NOT NICE.</i>

45
00:03:35,027 --> 00:03:36,561
<i>I'M STILL A DUCK.</i>

46
00:03:36,561 --> 00:03:37,961
<i>AND OUTSIDE THE WINDOW,</i>

47
00:03:37,961 --> 00:03:40,127
<i>THE SKY IS AS WIDE OPEN</i>
<i>AS EVER.</i>

48
00:03:40,127 --> 00:03:42,527
THERE'S NO PROBLEM!

49
00:03:42,527 --> 00:03:45,561
[ BELLS RINGING ]

50
00:03:59,094 --> 00:04:03,794
<i>-[ Thinking ] I AM RUE.</i>
<i>I'M NOT ANYONE ELSE.</i>

51
00:04:03,794 --> 00:04:05,594
<i>THAT'S WHO I'VE ALWAYS BEEN.</i>

52
00:04:06,627 --> 00:04:11,094
<i>AND WHO I ALWAYS WILL BE.</i>

53
00:04:11,094 --> 00:04:13,161
[ GASPS ]
[ CAWS ]

54
00:04:16,227 --> 00:04:20,161
-RUE.
-YES, WHAT?

55
00:04:20,161 --> 00:04:22,494
I WANT TO KNOW.

56
00:04:22,494 --> 00:04:27,561
I WANT TO KNOW WHETHER
I LOVE YOU OR NOT, RUE.

57
00:04:27,561 --> 00:04:29,994
-I WANT TO HEAR YOU SAY
THAT YOU LOVE ME.

58
00:04:29,994 --> 00:04:32,861
-YES, RUE, I LOVE YOU.

59
00:04:32,861 --> 00:04:36,461
-TRUST ME, MYTHO,
YOU DO LOVE ME.

60
00:04:36,461 --> 00:04:38,794
-OKAY. THEN I DO LOVE YOU.

61
00:04:38,794 --> 00:04:41,027
DO I REALLY LOVE YOU?

62
00:04:41,027 --> 00:04:43,594
-YOU DO.

63
00:04:43,594 --> 00:04:47,961
-THEN WHAT IS THIS THAT I FEEL
WHEN I'M THINKING OF TUTU?

64
00:04:47,961 --> 00:04:49,061
-[ SCOFFS ]

65
00:04:49,061 --> 00:04:51,261
TUTU.

66
00:04:51,261 --> 00:04:54,261
-RUE, MAYBE I'M ACTUALLY...

67
00:04:54,261 --> 00:04:56,127
-DON'T BOTHER ME
WITH THAT NONSENSE!

68
00:04:56,127 --> 00:04:59,861
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

69
00:04:59,861 --> 00:05:03,461
-WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN!
-RUINED? WILL THEY BE RUINED?

70
00:05:03,461 --> 00:05:06,961
OH, THEY'LL BE RUINED,
WON'T THEY?

71
00:05:06,961 --> 00:05:12,461
-WITH THIS HAND,
I TRIED TO PIERCE MYTHO'S HEART.

72
00:05:15,127 --> 00:05:17,261
ON THE GROUNDS THAT DOING SO

73
00:05:17,261 --> 00:05:19,827
WOULD BE
IN MYTHO'S BEST INTERESTS.

74
00:05:19,827 --> 00:05:24,394
BUT SINCE MYTHO HIMSELF WISHES
TO REGAIN HIS HEART,

75
00:05:24,394 --> 00:05:30,061
WHAT CAN I DO NOW THAT
NOTHING I DO CAN DETER HIM?

76
00:05:30,061 --> 00:05:33,761
IS THERE ANYTHING AT ALL
THAT REMAINS FOR ME?

77
00:05:33,761 --> 00:05:38,527
OTHER THAN ACCEPTING FATE
BY HIS SIDE WITHOUT TREMBLING?

78
00:05:38,527 --> 00:05:41,427
[ GASPS ] TREMBLING.

79
00:05:41,427 --> 00:05:44,561
AM <i>I</i> THE ONE WHO'S AFRAID?

80
00:05:44,561 --> 00:05:46,594
-HOW 'BOUT THE PIZZERIA?
-WHAT?

81
00:05:46,594 --> 00:05:47,694
-YOU DON'T KNOW IT?

82
00:05:47,694 --> 00:05:49,994
IT'S THE RED BUILDING
ON CHURCH STREET.

83
00:05:49,994 --> 00:05:53,061
-NO, I DON'T.
SO WHAT ABOUT THIS PIZZERIA?

84
00:05:53,061 --> 00:05:54,727
-WHAT DO YOU THINK?
-UH...

85
00:05:54,727 --> 00:05:56,127
-COME ON, WHAT ELSE?
-HUH?

86
00:05:56,127 --> 00:05:57,261
-YOUR REVENGE!
-YOUR REVENGE!

87
00:05:57,261 --> 00:05:59,827
-WHAT?! WHAT REVENGE?

88
00:05:59,827 --> 00:06:01,661
-FOR YOUR CONFESSION, OF COURSE.
-HUH?

89
00:06:01,661 --> 00:06:03,927
-NOW THAT MYTHO AND RUE
HAVE FALLEN INTO RUIN,

90
00:06:03,927 --> 00:06:06,261
THIS IS YOUR CHANCE.

91
00:06:06,261 --> 00:06:07,561
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

92
00:06:07,561 --> 00:06:09,027
-WELL, YOUR CONFESSION
THE OTHER DAY

93
00:06:09,027 --> 00:06:10,361
WAS KIND OF LUKEWARM.

94
00:06:10,361 --> 00:06:12,694
-NO!
-NOW YOU CAN CONFESS AGAIN!

95
00:06:12,694 --> 00:06:14,194
-OR RATHER,
GET TURNED DOWN AGAIN.

96
00:06:14,194 --> 00:06:16,761
-THAT'S NOT WHAT IT WAS!
AND WHAT DO YOU MEAN "RUINED"?

97
00:06:16,761 --> 00:06:18,194
HUH? HUH?

98
00:06:18,194 --> 00:06:19,494
-[ SNICKERS ]

99
00:06:19,494 --> 00:06:21,027
-IN OTHER WORDS,
NOW'S YOUR CHANCE!

100
00:06:21,027 --> 00:06:22,194
-CONFESSION! CONFESSION!

101
00:06:22,194 --> 00:06:23,761
-NO, I CAN'T!

102
00:06:23,761 --> 00:06:26,161
-YOU BIG COWARD!

103
00:06:26,161 --> 00:06:28,027
-[ GROANS ]

104
00:06:28,027 --> 00:06:29,627
-YOU SHOULD ROLL DOWN
THE HALLWAY!

105
00:06:29,627 --> 00:06:31,194
-IT'S YOUR FAULT!
-REALLY?

106
00:06:31,194 --> 00:06:33,761
-YOU AGAIN, MISS DUCK?
[ GROANS ]

107
00:06:33,761 --> 00:06:35,327
ROLLING DOWN THE HALLWAY.

108
00:06:35,327 --> 00:06:37,527
IF YOU KEEP THIS UP,

109
00:06:37,527 --> 00:06:40,761
I WILL HAVE NO CHOICE
BUT TO HAVE YOU MARRY ME!

110
00:06:40,761 --> 00:06:44,061
-I-I AM SO SORRY!

111
00:06:44,061 --> 00:06:46,327
SOMETHING'S ROLLING DOWN
THE HALL!

112
00:06:46,327 --> 00:06:48,561
IT'S COMING REALLY FAST!

113
00:06:48,561 --> 00:06:49,861
-[ SCREAMS ]

114
00:06:49,861 --> 00:06:51,227
WHAT?

115
00:06:51,227 --> 00:06:52,361
[ GASPS ]

116
00:06:52,361 --> 00:06:53,861
MS. GOATETTE.

117
00:06:53,861 --> 00:06:55,261
-IF YOU ROLL DOWN THE HALLWAY,

118
00:06:55,261 --> 00:06:58,661
YOU'LL BE FORCED TO MARRY
MR. CAT!

119
00:06:58,661 --> 00:06:59,927
-[ HISSES ]

120
00:06:59,927 --> 00:07:03,327
[ MEOWS ]

121
00:07:07,127 --> 00:07:10,727
[ DOOR OPENS ]

122
00:07:10,727 --> 00:07:14,194
-YOU AGAIN, HUH?
COME TO READ THAT BOOK?

123
00:07:17,227 --> 00:07:19,894
<i>♪</i>

124
00:07:19,894 --> 00:07:21,994
-HEY, WHAT ABOUT INVITING HIM
TO YOUR HOUSE?

125
00:07:21,994 --> 00:07:23,027
-HOUSE?

126
00:07:23,027 --> 00:07:24,994
-OH! WHERE <i>IS</i> YOUR HOUSE, DUCK?

127
00:07:24,994 --> 00:07:26,294
-UH, THE LAKE.
-THE LAKE?

128
00:07:26,294 --> 00:07:27,427
-THE LAKE?

129
00:07:27,427 --> 00:07:29,227
-I MEAN, IT'S OUT
TOWARDS THE LAKE.

130
00:07:29,227 --> 00:07:31,394
-SO I GUESS IT'S OUTSIDE TOWN,
HUH?

131
00:07:31,394 --> 00:07:35,061
-AFTER ALL, THE ONLY THING
IN TOWN IS THAT POND.

132
00:07:35,061 --> 00:07:36,661
-ALL RIGHT, EVERYONE,
THAT WILL BE IT

133
00:07:36,661 --> 00:07:38,361
FOR THE BEGINNER CLASS LESSON.

134
00:07:38,361 --> 00:07:39,427
THE NEXT HOUR --

135
00:07:39,427 --> 00:07:40,894
[ DOOR OPENS ]
-[ MEOWS ]

136
00:07:43,994 --> 00:07:46,694
[ YOWLS ]

137
00:07:46,694 --> 00:07:49,194
THE PRIVATE LESSON
FOR THE ADVANCED CLASS

138
00:07:49,194 --> 00:07:50,227
WILL BE STARTING AFTER THIS,

139
00:07:50,227 --> 00:07:52,127
SO PLEASE VACATE THE ROOM
IMMEDIATELY.

140
00:07:52,127 --> 00:07:56,694
IF YOU DAWDLE OR HANG ABOUT,
I WILL HAVE YOU MARRY ME!

141
00:07:56,694 --> 00:07:58,461
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

142
00:07:58,461 --> 00:08:01,694
UH, MS. GOATETTE'S
DAWDLING AND HANGING ABOUT.

143
00:08:01,694 --> 00:08:03,761
-IT SEEMS YOU'LL HAVE
TO GET MARRIED.

144
00:08:03,761 --> 00:08:08,361
-[ YOWLING ]

145
00:08:08,361 --> 00:08:11,194
-[ BLEATS ]

146
00:08:11,194 --> 00:08:13,061
-HUH?

147
00:08:14,894 --> 00:08:15,927
-[ ALL GASPING ]
-MYTHO.

148
00:08:15,927 --> 00:08:17,061
-YOUR CHANCE!
-YOUR CHANCE!

149
00:08:18,361 --> 00:08:21,361
-[ GASPS ]
-OH.

150
00:08:21,361 --> 00:08:24,394
♪

151
00:08:28,227 --> 00:08:29,794
-WONDERFUL AS EVER, HUH?

152
00:08:29,794 --> 00:08:32,861
-DOESN'T LOOK LIKE
THERE'S AN OPENING FOR DUCK.

153
00:08:32,861 --> 00:08:34,894
-DON'T LOSE HEART, DUCK.
-THAT'S RIGHT.

154
00:08:34,894 --> 00:08:38,094
AFTER ALL, WE ALREADY KNEW
THIS WAS THE CASE.

155
00:08:39,994 --> 00:08:41,594
<i>-[ Thinking ] I KNOW.</i>

156
00:08:41,594 --> 00:08:44,627
<i>MYTHO IS PERFECT FOR RUE.</i>

157
00:08:46,627 --> 00:08:49,694
<i>[ Thinking ]</i>
<i>I KNOW THAT I'M JUST A DUCK.</i>

158
00:08:49,694 --> 00:08:51,461
-WHAT DO YOU THINK OF ME?

159
00:08:51,461 --> 00:08:53,494
I WANT TO KNOW.

160
00:08:53,494 --> 00:08:58,061
<i>-[ Thinking ] I KNOW EXACTLY</i>
<i>WHAT I THINK OF MYTHO.</i>

161
00:08:58,061 --> 00:08:59,694
<i>BUT I CAN'T SAY IT.</i>

162
00:08:59,694 --> 00:09:01,994
-IF YOU CHOOSE
TO BECOME PRINCESS TUTU,

163
00:09:01,994 --> 00:09:04,127
YOU CAN SAVE YOUR DEAR PRINCE.

164
00:09:04,127 --> 00:09:06,261
BUT IF YOU PROCLAIM
YOUR LOVE TO HIM,

165
00:09:06,261 --> 00:09:09,194
YOU'LL TURN INTO
A SPECK OF LIGHT AND VANISH.

166
00:09:09,194 --> 00:09:10,694
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

167
00:09:10,694 --> 00:09:12,194
<i>-[ Thinking ] I KNOW,</i>

168
00:09:12,194 --> 00:09:16,227
<i>BUT SOMEHOW</i>
<i>MY HEART STILL ACHES.</i>

169
00:09:16,227 --> 00:09:18,227
<i>-[ Thinking ] YOU DON'T HAVE TO</i>
<i>CHANGE AT ALL.</i>

170
00:09:18,227 --> 00:09:20,227
<i>YOU'RE FINE JUST AS YOU ARE.</i>

171
00:09:20,227 --> 00:09:24,061
<i>WHY MUST YOU KEEP TRYING</i>
<i>TO CHANGE WHEN I DON'T WANT TO,</i>

172
00:09:24,061 --> 00:09:27,027
<i>WHEN I WANT THINGS</i>
<i>TO STAY AS THEY ARE?</i>

173
00:09:30,194 --> 00:09:31,627
-[ GASPS ]

174
00:09:31,627 --> 00:09:34,427
PRINCESS TUTU.

175
00:09:35,961 --> 00:09:40,194
-WHAT IN THE WORLD IS THERE
THAT I NEED FEAR?

176
00:09:40,194 --> 00:09:41,994
[ PAGES RUSTLE ]

177
00:09:41,994 --> 00:09:43,061
-RIDICULOUS.

178
00:09:43,061 --> 00:09:44,994
"THE PRINCE AND THE CROW."

179
00:09:44,994 --> 00:09:48,694
THE STORY THAT IS WRITTEN HERE
IS MYTHO'S TALE.

180
00:09:48,694 --> 00:09:51,861
THE FATE OF A FOOLISH PRINCE
WHO TRIED TO PROTECT THE WEAK,

181
00:09:51,861 --> 00:09:53,661
BUT ONLY ENDED UP
HURTING HIMSELF

182
00:09:53,661 --> 00:09:56,694
AND LOSING HIS OWN HEART.

183
00:09:56,694 --> 00:09:58,094
THAT'S ALL.

184
00:09:58,094 --> 00:10:02,527
-MAY THOSE WHO ACCEPT
THEIR FATE BE GRANTED HAPPINESS.

185
00:10:02,527 --> 00:10:06,494
MAY THOSE WHO DEFY IT,
BE GRANTED GLORY.

186
00:10:06,494 --> 00:10:09,327
-YOU'RE --
-THE STORY IS CONTINUING.

187
00:10:09,327 --> 00:10:11,227
THE STORY IS ALIVE.

188
00:10:19,527 --> 00:10:23,594
-ARE YOU SAYING
THIS IS MY FATE?

189
00:10:23,594 --> 00:10:24,927
-[ SIGHS ]

190
00:10:24,927 --> 00:10:28,361
IS IT SAD FOR MYTHO, FOR RUE,

191
00:10:28,361 --> 00:10:31,861
FOR DUCK, OR FOR...

192
00:10:34,594 --> 00:10:38,894
[ CLATTERING ]

193
00:10:38,894 --> 00:10:40,327
-YOU KNOW, RUE,

194
00:10:40,327 --> 00:10:42,694
YOU REALLY DANCE BEAUTIFULLY
<i>EN POINTE.</i>

195
00:10:42,694 --> 00:10:46,161
AND WHEN YOU AND MYTHO DANCE,
IT'S ALWAYS SO WONDERFUL.

196
00:10:46,161 --> 00:10:49,594
I'D LOVE TO DANCE LIKE THAT,
BUT THERE'S NO WAY I CAN YET.

197
00:10:49,594 --> 00:10:50,827
-DID YOU WANT SOMETHING?

198
00:10:50,827 --> 00:10:54,027
-OH. UH, WELL...

199
00:10:54,027 --> 00:10:56,694
EARLIER YOU MENTIONED
PRINCESS TUTU.

200
00:10:56,694 --> 00:10:59,827
-JUST WHAT ARE YOU
PRATTLING ON ABOUT?

201
00:10:59,827 --> 00:11:04,061
A FAIRY TALE LIKE THAT
IS OF NO IMPORTANCE.

202
00:11:04,061 --> 00:11:05,727
-YOU'RE YOUR USUAL SELF.

203
00:11:05,727 --> 00:11:08,727
-OF COURSE I AM.
I'M NOT GOING TO CHANGE.

204
00:11:08,727 --> 00:11:10,694
IF YOU WANNA SAY SOMETHING,
HURRY UP.

205
00:11:10,694 --> 00:11:13,061
-THERE'S NOTHING REALLY.

206
00:11:13,061 --> 00:11:15,861
YOU KNOW, I THINK THE FIRST
PERSON TO DANCE <i>EN POINTE</i>

207
00:11:15,861 --> 00:11:18,761
WAS INCREDIBLE! DON'T YOU?

208
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:20,194
-THERE'S A STORY ABOUT
THE TOE SHOES

209
00:11:20,194 --> 00:11:22,861
OF THE FIRST PERSON
TO DANCE <i>EN POINTE.</i>

210
00:11:22,861 --> 00:11:24,461
DO YOU KNOW WHAT HAPPENED
TO THEM?

211
00:11:24,461 --> 00:11:26,461
-WHAT? UH, NO.

212
00:11:26,461 --> 00:11:28,127
-WELL, THEY WERE EATEN.

213
00:11:28,127 --> 00:11:29,327
-THEY WHAT?!

214
00:11:29,327 --> 00:11:32,761
-BY A PERSON TO WORSHIPPED
THAT BALLERINA.

215
00:11:32,761 --> 00:11:34,694
-THAT'S KIND OF AMAZING.

216
00:11:34,694 --> 00:11:36,427
-IT'S A STUPID STORY.

217
00:11:36,427 --> 00:11:38,794
-HUH?

218
00:11:38,794 --> 00:11:40,027
-STRANGE.

219
00:11:40,027 --> 00:11:42,694
-WHAT?! NO! WHERE? HUH?
WHAT'S STRANGE?

220
00:11:42,694 --> 00:11:44,261
HUH? HUH? HUH? HUH? HUH?

221
00:11:44,261 --> 00:11:47,594
-I'VE NEVER TALKED LIKE THIS
WITH ANOTHER GIRL BEFORE.

222
00:11:47,594 --> 00:11:49,027
-OH.

223
00:11:49,027 --> 00:11:52,261
DO YOU HATE THIS KIND OF THING?

224
00:11:52,261 --> 00:11:54,794
-I DON'T THINK I HATE IT.

225
00:11:54,794 --> 00:11:58,827
-I'M GLAD. SO WE CAN BECOME
EVEN BETTER FRIENDS, RIGHT?

226
00:11:58,827 --> 00:11:59,894
-YOU THINK?

227
00:11:59,894 --> 00:12:01,494
-HEY, HEY, RUE.

228
00:12:01,494 --> 00:12:03,961
TEACH ME ABOUT GOING <i>EN POINTE.</i>
-AND WHY SHOULD I TEACH YOU?

229
00:12:03,961 --> 00:12:06,094
-BECAUSE WE'RE FRIENDS.

230
00:12:06,094 --> 00:12:08,361
-YOU'VE GOT A LOT OF CHEEK.

231
00:12:08,361 --> 00:12:09,927
-HEY, RUE?
-NOW WHAT?

232
00:12:09,927 --> 00:12:12,361
-UM, IS THAT GIRL
YOUR FRIEND, TOO? [ GASPS ]

233
00:12:12,361 --> 00:12:14,461
-WHERE? WHAT GIRL IS THIS?

234
00:12:14,461 --> 00:12:17,327
-SHE DISAPPEARED. [ LAUGHS ]

235
00:12:17,327 --> 00:12:19,027
-[ SIGHS ]

236
00:12:19,027 --> 00:12:22,061
[ TCHAIKOVSKY'S "DANCE OF
THE SUGAR PLUM FAIRY" PLAYING ]

237
00:12:32,683 --> 00:12:35,450
-AND THAT CONCLUDES
TODAY'S LECTURE ON --

238
00:12:35,450 --> 00:12:36,950
-[ BLEATS ]
-[ YOWLS ]

239
00:12:36,950 --> 00:12:38,517
-GOOD-BYE, MISS RUE.
-GOOD-BYE, MISS RUE.

240
00:12:38,517 --> 00:12:40,883
SEE YOU LATER.
-I BID YOU GOOD AFTERNOON.

241
00:12:43,383 --> 00:12:45,717
-DO YOUR BEST IN DETENTION!

242
00:12:45,717 --> 00:12:48,750
-DON'T BE GLUM. YOUR FEATHERS
ARE WHAT MAKE YOU, DUCK.

243
00:12:48,750 --> 00:12:51,483
-SO, DUCK,
YOU CAN'T GO HOME YET?

244
00:12:51,483 --> 00:12:52,883
-HUH?
-HUH?

245
00:12:52,883 --> 00:12:55,383
-YEAH, I HAVE TO STAY AND WIPE
THE WINDOWS AS PUNISHMENT.

246
00:12:55,383 --> 00:12:59,450
-OH.

247
00:12:59,450 --> 00:13:01,917
FRIENDS.

248
00:13:01,917 --> 00:13:04,517
[ RAVENS CAWING ]

249
00:13:12,317 --> 00:13:15,683
-[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

250
00:13:15,683 --> 00:13:18,183
THAT'S THE GIRL FROM...

251
00:13:18,183 --> 00:13:19,317
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

252
00:13:21,183 --> 00:13:25,517
-SHE WENT INTO THE ART BUILDING.
SO SHE STUDIES DRAWING, HUH?

253
00:13:25,517 --> 00:13:30,017
[ RAVENS CAWING ]

254
00:13:30,017 --> 00:13:31,750
-HI, RUE!

255
00:13:33,783 --> 00:13:38,183
-LADY...RUE?

256
00:13:38,183 --> 00:13:39,750
-WHAT? WHAT'S SO HARD
ABOUT THAT?

257
00:13:41,550 --> 00:13:44,250
-BESIDES, WE'VE WALKED TOGETHER
AND TALKED ALL THIS TIME,

258
00:13:44,250 --> 00:13:46,250
SO WE'RE ALREADY FRIENDS NOW.

259
00:13:46,250 --> 00:13:47,350
RUE.

260
00:13:49,217 --> 00:13:52,250
YOU'RE LIKE A REAL PRINCESS
AND YOU REALLY SUIT EACH OTHER,

261
00:13:52,250 --> 00:13:54,983
SO I'M SURE YOU'LL GET
THE GOLDEN APPLE, TOO.

262
00:13:54,983 --> 00:13:57,883
<i>YOU REALLY SUIT EACH OTHER,</i>
<i>SO...</i>

263
00:13:57,883 --> 00:13:59,283
-SUIT EACH OTHER?

264
00:13:59,283 --> 00:14:01,917
-IT'S JUST AN IDEA
YOU'VE GOT STUCK IN YOUR HEAD.

265
00:14:01,917 --> 00:14:03,483
-[ BLEATING ]

266
00:14:03,483 --> 00:14:05,850
-OH, YOU MAY THINK YOU NEED ME
BUT THE SIMPLE FACT REMAINS,

267
00:14:05,850 --> 00:14:07,750
I DO NOT NEED YOU.

268
00:14:07,750 --> 00:14:09,050
-[ BLEATS ]

269
00:14:09,050 --> 00:14:11,450
<i>-[ Thinking ]</i>
<i>THE PERSON I NEED IS MYTHO.</i>

270
00:14:11,450 --> 00:14:14,250
<i>BUT THE ONE MYTHO NEEDS IS...</i>

271
00:14:16,017 --> 00:14:19,217
<i>PRINCESS TUTU.</i>

272
00:14:21,250 --> 00:14:25,217
-I WONDER WHAT IT IS
I THINK OF YOU, FAKIR.

273
00:14:27,083 --> 00:14:31,183
-WHEN I THINK OF RUE,
WHEN I THINK OF YOU, FAKIR,

274
00:14:31,183 --> 00:14:34,550
AND WHEN I'M THINKING ABOUT
PRINCESS TUTU,

275
00:14:34,550 --> 00:14:36,717
EACH ONE MAKES ME FEEL
DIFFERENT.

276
00:14:38,350 --> 00:14:40,817
I'VE CHOSEN TO GO, FAKIR.

277
00:14:40,817 --> 00:14:42,883
-YOU'RE KIDDING, RIGHT?
-I MEAN IT.

278
00:14:42,883 --> 00:14:44,150
-WHAT POINT IS THERE?

279
00:14:44,150 --> 00:14:46,917
-MAYBE THERE'S SOMETHING
SHE CAN TELL ME ABOUT TUTU.

280
00:14:46,917 --> 00:14:49,717
-MYTHO'S CHANGING INTO...

281
00:14:49,717 --> 00:14:51,750
A MYTHO THAT I DON'T KNOW.

282
00:14:51,750 --> 00:14:54,117
-THAT IS SOMETHING
THAT CANNOT BE HELPED.

283
00:14:54,117 --> 00:14:56,750
THE WAY WE THINK ABOUT THINGS
IS WORLDS APART.

284
00:14:56,750 --> 00:14:58,417
-[ CHEWING ]

285
00:14:58,417 --> 00:15:01,850
-AS YOU CAN SEE, EVEN WHAT
WE EAT IS QUITE DIFFERENT.

286
00:15:01,850 --> 00:15:05,450
IT IS FOR THESE REASONS THAT
I DO NOT WISH TO MARRY YOU.

287
00:15:05,450 --> 00:15:08,883
AND SO I'VE NO INTENTION
OF CHANGING MY WILL!

288
00:15:08,883 --> 00:15:11,883
-[ GASPS ] MY WILL.

289
00:15:11,883 --> 00:15:15,183
-DO YOU UNDERSTAND ME NOW,
MISS GOATETTE?

290
00:15:15,183 --> 00:15:16,783
-[ BLEATS ]

291
00:15:16,783 --> 00:15:19,850
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

292
00:15:19,850 --> 00:15:22,950
[ PENCIL SCRAPING ]

293
00:15:22,950 --> 00:15:24,450
-UM, HELLO?

294
00:15:24,450 --> 00:15:26,350
-YOU'RE ONE OF
THE BALLET STUDENTS.

295
00:15:26,350 --> 00:15:29,650
-WELL, I'M REALLY PRETTY
TERRIBLE AT DRAWING PICTURES.

296
00:15:29,650 --> 00:15:31,350
-THAT'S BECAUSE
YOU'RE IN BALLET.

297
00:15:31,350 --> 00:15:32,917
-I'M BAD AT BALLET, TOO, THOUGH.

298
00:15:32,917 --> 00:15:35,283
-OH! YOU ARE? I'M SORRY!

299
00:15:35,283 --> 00:15:38,283
-NO, NO, IT'S FINE.
MIND IF I TAKE A PEEK?

300
00:15:38,283 --> 00:15:39,517
-WOW, IT'S GREAT!

301
00:15:39,517 --> 00:15:41,083
A DRAWING OF RUE.

302
00:15:41,083 --> 00:15:42,917
I'M SO JEALOUS OF YOU.

303
00:15:42,917 --> 00:15:45,117
OH. DID YOU DRAW
THESE ONES, TOO?

304
00:15:45,117 --> 00:15:46,583
-MM-HMM.
-HANG ON.

305
00:15:46,583 --> 00:15:50,050
THEY'RE ALL DRAWINGS OF RUE?

306
00:15:50,050 --> 00:15:53,750
WELL, RUE REALLY IS PRETTY,
SO I CAN TOTALLY UNDERSTAND.

307
00:15:53,750 --> 00:15:55,683
HEY, THIS ONE'S SIGNED.

308
00:15:55,683 --> 00:15:57,017
YOUR NAME IS MALEN?

309
00:15:57,017 --> 00:16:00,150
HEY, THAT'S A CUTE NAME!
MY NAME'S DUCK!

310
00:16:00,150 --> 00:16:01,883
-I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
-HUH?

311
00:16:01,883 --> 00:16:04,850
-I DON'T...REALLY UNDERSTAND IT,
MYSELF.

312
00:16:04,850 --> 00:16:07,250
I MEAN, I'VE ALWAYS ENJOYED

313
00:16:07,250 --> 00:16:09,883
DOING LIFE DRAWING
WITH MISS RUE AS THE MODEL,

314
00:16:09,883 --> 00:16:13,283
BUT IT USED TO BE I WANTED
TO DRAW OTHER THINGS, TOO,

315
00:16:13,283 --> 00:16:15,450
LIKE FRUITS AND SCENERIES.

316
00:16:15,450 --> 00:16:16,650
-OH.

317
00:16:16,650 --> 00:16:19,917
-BUT NOW
I CAN ONLY DRAW MISS RUE.

318
00:16:22,583 --> 00:16:26,250
<i>-[ Thinking ] PRINCESS TUTU?</i>

319
00:16:31,417 --> 00:16:35,150
<i>PRINCESS TUTU</i>
<i>WILL CHANGE EVERYTHING.</i>

320
00:16:35,150 --> 00:16:37,517
<i>SHE'LL CHANGE MYTHO.</i>

321
00:16:37,517 --> 00:16:41,950
<i>AT THIS RATE, MYTHO WILL ONLY</i>
<i>GROW MORE DISTANT FROM ME.</i>

322
00:16:41,950 --> 00:16:43,950
<i>I WON'T ALLOW THAT TO HAPPEN.</i>

323
00:16:43,950 --> 00:16:46,850
-THEN WHAT DO YOU PLAN
TO DO ABOUT IT?

324
00:16:46,850 --> 00:16:48,083
[ CLACKING ]
-[ GASPS ]

325
00:16:48,083 --> 00:16:49,617
WHAT?

326
00:16:49,617 --> 00:16:52,450
-A BEAUTIFUL BLACK SWAN.

327
00:16:55,350 --> 00:16:58,517
-WHO <i>IS</i> THE HEROINE
OF THIS STORY?

328
00:16:58,517 --> 00:17:00,683
IS IT PRINCESS TUTU

329
00:17:00,683 --> 00:17:03,550
OR IS IT PRINCESS KRAEHE?

330
00:17:03,550 --> 00:17:05,752
-PRINCESS KRAEHE THE HEROINE?

331
00:17:09,535 --> 00:17:13,435
-IT HURTS WHEN I TRY
TO DRAW ANYTHING ELSE.

332
00:17:13,435 --> 00:17:17,235
[ CHIME ]
-OH.

333
00:17:17,235 --> 00:17:21,668
-A STORY DOESN'T NEED
TWO HEROINES NOW, DOES IT?

334
00:17:21,668 --> 00:17:25,102
AND NO PRINCE NEEDS
TWO PRINCESSES.

335
00:17:25,102 --> 00:17:28,335
NOW COME AND TELL ME
WHAT SHOULD HAPPEN NEXT.

336
00:17:28,335 --> 00:17:29,668
[ CHIMING ]

337
00:17:29,668 --> 00:17:30,968
[ BUBBLING ]

338
00:17:30,968 --> 00:17:34,002
[ TINKLING ]

339
00:17:43,202 --> 00:17:48,035
-[ CRYING ]

340
00:17:48,035 --> 00:17:52,802
-PLEASE, COME DANCE WITH ME,
MISS MALEN.

341
00:17:52,802 --> 00:17:53,802
-WHO ARE YOU?

342
00:17:53,802 --> 00:17:55,535
I DON'T KNOW HOW TO DANCE.

343
00:17:55,535 --> 00:17:59,268
-DON'T WORRY.
JUST DANCE FREELY.

344
00:17:59,268 --> 00:18:02,268
-[ GASPS ]

345
00:18:02,268 --> 00:18:05,302
-THE SOURCE OF YOUR PAIN
IS THE FALSE HEART

346
00:18:05,302 --> 00:18:07,868
RESIDING IN YOUR HEART.

347
00:18:07,868 --> 00:18:10,235
I'LL REMOVE IT FOR YOU.

348
00:18:10,235 --> 00:18:14,868
THEN, ONCE AGAIN, YOU'LL BE ABLE
TO DRAW WHAT YOU LOVE.

349
00:18:14,868 --> 00:18:16,468
-REALLY?
-YES.

350
00:18:16,468 --> 00:18:20,035
YOU CAN GO BACK TO BEING
YOUR OLD SELF.

351
00:18:20,035 --> 00:18:23,835
-THANK YOU. I'M SO GLAD.

352
00:18:23,835 --> 00:18:26,902
[ HUMMING ]

353
00:18:26,902 --> 00:18:30,768
[ MUSSORGSKY'S
"IL VECCHIO CASTELLO" PLAYING ]

354
00:18:30,768 --> 00:18:35,135
-I JUST WANT TO STAY THE SAME,
NEVER CHANGING.

355
00:18:35,135 --> 00:18:38,268
[ RAVENS CAWING, WINGS FLUTTER ]

356
00:18:38,268 --> 00:18:40,135
[ CAWS ]

357
00:18:40,135 --> 00:18:46,268
-YES, ONCE AGAIN,
PRINCESS TUTU...

358
00:18:46,268 --> 00:18:48,802
HAS CHANGED MYTHO.

359
00:18:48,802 --> 00:18:51,102
[ WIND GUSTS ]

360
00:19:07,068 --> 00:19:08,135
[ WIND GUSTING ]

361
00:19:08,135 --> 00:19:09,535
-AAH!

362
00:19:09,535 --> 00:19:10,702
NO!

363
00:19:10,702 --> 00:19:13,535
[ SCREAMING ]

364
00:19:28,302 --> 00:19:30,802
[ RAVENS CAWING ]

365
00:19:30,802 --> 00:19:33,302
-WHAT'S THIS?

366
00:19:33,302 --> 00:19:37,235
-TUTU, WHERE ARE YOU?

367
00:19:37,235 --> 00:19:39,268
HUH?

368
00:19:41,802 --> 00:19:44,535
-WHAT EMOTION ARE YOU?

369
00:19:44,535 --> 00:19:47,268
-I'M THE FEELING OF DEVOTION.

370
00:19:47,268 --> 00:19:49,568
-YOU ARE A SHARD OF
THE PRINCE'S HEART

371
00:19:49,568 --> 00:19:50,768
WHICH HE LOST.

372
00:19:52,635 --> 00:19:53,802
[ WIND BLOWS ]

373
00:19:53,802 --> 00:19:57,302
-SO THE FEELING OF DEVOTION,
IS IT?

374
00:19:57,302 --> 00:19:58,702
-KRAEHE.

375
00:19:58,702 --> 00:20:02,035
-I WILL NOT SUFFER YOU
TO RETURN SUCH A THING TO MYTHO.

376
00:20:02,035 --> 00:20:03,202
-WHAT WILL YOU DO?

377
00:20:03,202 --> 00:20:05,435
-I DON'T KNOW.
WHAT SHOULD I DO?

378
00:20:05,435 --> 00:20:07,568
[ RAVENS CAWING ]
-[ GASPS ]

379
00:20:13,835 --> 00:20:15,235
-[ GASPS ] NO!

380
00:20:15,235 --> 00:20:16,935
[ WIND GUSTS ]
-AH!

381
00:20:16,935 --> 00:20:19,435
[ GROANS ]
-[ LAUGHS ]

382
00:20:19,435 --> 00:20:20,902
YOU HAD BETTER FORGET
ABOUT RESTORING

383
00:20:20,902 --> 00:20:23,535
ANY MORE HEART SHARDS
TO THE PRINCE.

384
00:20:23,535 --> 00:20:25,102
-BUT THE PRINCE TOLD ME.

385
00:20:25,102 --> 00:20:28,468
THE PRINCE TOLD ME THAT
HE WANTS TO REGAIN HIS HEART!

386
00:20:28,468 --> 00:20:30,768
-HMM?

387
00:20:30,768 --> 00:20:31,868
[ GROANS ]

388
00:20:31,868 --> 00:20:34,102
-PRINCESS TUTU.

389
00:20:35,702 --> 00:20:37,635
I FINALLY FOUND YOU.

390
00:20:37,635 --> 00:20:39,235
[ GASPS ]

391
00:20:39,235 --> 00:20:41,768
KRAEHE.
-[ GASPS ]

392
00:20:41,768 --> 00:20:45,602
WHY DO YOU LOOK AT ME THAT WAY?

393
00:20:45,602 --> 00:20:46,702
AM I...

394
00:20:46,702 --> 00:20:47,968
[ GASPS ]

395
00:20:47,968 --> 00:20:51,235
-AM I...[ CRYING ]

396
00:20:51,235 --> 00:20:53,035
-KRAEHE.

397
00:20:53,035 --> 00:20:55,468
[ CHIMING ]

398
00:20:55,468 --> 00:20:56,968
-[ CRYING ]

399
00:20:56,968 --> 00:21:00,502
-WHAT'S WRONG?
-STAY AWAY!

400
00:21:00,502 --> 00:21:02,968
[ SOBBING ]

401
00:21:02,968 --> 00:21:07,435
<i>-[ Thinking ]</i>
<i>AM I...NOT NEEDED?</i>

402
00:21:15,468 --> 00:21:20,302
-KRAEHE, WHY ARE YOU
IN SUCH PAIN?

403
00:21:20,302 --> 00:21:21,535
-WHAT?

404
00:21:21,535 --> 00:21:26,235
-IS THERE ANY WAY
I CAN HELP YOU?

405
00:21:26,235 --> 00:21:28,468
-WHO IS KRAEHE?

406
00:21:28,468 --> 00:21:29,935
[ GLASS SHATTERS ]
-[ GASPS ]

407
00:21:31,368 --> 00:21:33,802
-FAKIR!
[ GLASS SHATTERS ]

408
00:21:33,802 --> 00:21:36,502
-BE GONE, YOU UGLY CROW!

409
00:21:36,502 --> 00:21:38,802
-CROW?

410
00:21:42,068 --> 00:21:43,968
-[ CHUCKLES ]

411
00:21:43,968 --> 00:21:46,402
THAT'S RIGHT, I <i>AM</i> A CROW.

412
00:21:46,402 --> 00:21:49,302
AND I, ALONE,
AM THE TRUE PRIMA DONNA

413
00:21:49,302 --> 00:21:51,635
PRINCESS KRAEHE.

414
00:21:51,635 --> 00:21:55,368
I'LL TAKE WHAT I DESIRE
BY FORCE IF NEED BE.

415
00:21:58,568 --> 00:22:04,568
[ RAVENS CAWING ]

416
00:22:04,568 --> 00:22:07,602
[ RITSUKO OKAZAKI'S "ALTHOUGH
MY LOVE IS SMALL" PLAYING ]

417
00:22:17,368 --> 00:22:19,302
<i>-♪ YUME MIRU ♪</i>

418
00:22:19,302 --> 00:22:21,668
<i>♪ YOU NI ♪</i>

419
00:22:21,668 --> 00:22:24,502
<i>♪ KOI O SHITA NO ♪</i>

420
00:22:27,702 --> 00:22:30,368
<i>♪ FUKURAMU ♪</i>

421
00:22:30,368 --> 00:22:35,335
<i>♪ KOKORO GA FUKURAMU NO YO ♪</i>

422
00:22:35,335 --> 00:22:40,002
<i>♪ IKITERUTTE SUTEKI</i>
<i>NA KOTO TO OMOTTA ♪</i>

423
00:22:42,902 --> 00:22:47,335
<i>♪ ASU GA MACHI DOOSHII ♪</i>

424
00:22:47,335 --> 00:22:49,068
<i>♪ MM ♪</i>

425
00:22:49,068 --> 00:22:56,168
<i>♪ ANATA NO CHIKARA NI NARITAI</i>
<i>NO DONNA TOKI NI MO WATASHI ♪</i>

426
00:22:56,168 --> 00:23:00,268
<i>♪ MATTE MATTE</i>
<i>KURENAI HASHITTE ♪</i>

427
00:23:00,268 --> 00:23:02,835
<i>♪ HASHITTE IKU NO YO ♪</i>

428
00:23:02,835 --> 00:23:08,902
<i>♪ KAZE MO AMAGUMO</i>
<i>MO OIKOSHITE ♪</i>

429
00:23:08,902 --> 00:23:16,102
<i>♪ WATASHI DAKE</i>
<i>NO TSUBASA HABATAITE ♪</i>

430
00:23:34,502 --> 00:23:37,502
-MYTHO AND KRAEHE'S WEDDING?

431
00:23:37,502 --> 00:23:39,735
WITH FAKIR FOR A WITNESS?

432
00:23:39,735 --> 00:23:41,235
-THE LEGEND YOU TOLD ME ABOUT
AS A CHILD

433
00:23:41,235 --> 00:23:43,302
IS SWIFTLY BECOMING REALITY.

434
00:23:43,302 --> 00:23:46,535
YOU'D BE MUCH BETTER OFF
FORGETTING THIS ACCURSED TALE.

435
00:23:46,535 --> 00:23:49,735
"PRINCE" IS A WEIRD NAME.
HOW 'BOUT WE CALL YOU MYTHO?

436
00:23:49,735 --> 00:23:51,268
-ARE YOU GOING TO KRAEHE?

437
00:23:51,268 --> 00:23:53,068
-I FEEL I MUST RUN AWAY.

438
00:23:53,068 --> 00:23:55,002
-WHAT SAY YOU, PRINCESS TUTU?

439
00:23:55,002 --> 00:23:57,502
AREN'T WE JUST PERFECT
FOR EACH OTHER?

440
00:23:57,502 --> 00:24:01,002
-ALL WHO LOVE STORIES,
GATHER 'ROUND.

441
00:24:01,002 --> 00:24:04,435
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

